{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@interface"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMapSnapshotter"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"NSObject","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSObject"}],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can change the snapshotter’s options at any time and reuse the snapshotter","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for multiple distinct snapshots; however, the snapshotter can only generate one","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"snapshot at a time. If you need to generate multiple snapshots concurrently,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"create multiple snapshotter objects.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For an interactive map, use the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","type":"reference"},{"text":" class. Both ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","type":"reference"},{"text":" are compatible with offline packs managed by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOfflineStorage","type":"reference"},{"text":" class.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"From a snapshot, you can obtain an image and convert geographic coordinates to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the image’s coordinate space in order to superimpose markers and overlays. If"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you do not need offline map functionality, you can use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Snapshot"},{"type":"text","text":" class in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/mapbox\/MapboxStatic.swift\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to generate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"static map images with overlays."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Example","anchor":"Example","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let camera = MLNMapCamera(lookingAtCenter: CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 37.7184, longitude:","-122.4365), altitude: 100, pitch: 20, heading: 0)","","let options = MLNMapSnapshotOptions(styleURL: MLNStyle.satelliteStreetsStyleURL, camera: camera,","size: CGSize(width: 320, height: 480)) options.zoomLevel = 10","","let snapshotter = MLNMapSnapshotter(options: options)","snapshotter.start { (snapshot, error) in","    if let error = error {","        fatalError(error.localizedDescription)","    }","","    image = snapshot?.image","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Related examples","anchor":"Related-examples","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TODO: Create a static map snapshot, learn how to use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter"},{"type":"text","text":" to generate a static image based on an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object’s style, camera, and view bounds."}]}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLN